### Power of Three Problem Solution in Java

#### Problem Description
Given an integer `n`, return `true` if it is a power of three. Otherwise, return `false`.

#### Solution

```java
public class Solution {
    /**
     * Checks if a given integer is a power of three.
     * 
     * @param n The input integer to check.
     * @return True if the integer is a power of three, false otherwise.
     */
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        // Handle edge cases
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        // Use logarithm to check if n is a power of three
        return Math.log(n) / Math.log(3) % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

#### Explanation
This solution uses the mathematical property that if `n` is a power of `3`, then `log(n) / log(3)` will be an integer. This is because `log(a^b) = b * log(a)`. Therefore, if `n` is a power of `3`, `log(n) / log(3)` will be an integer.

